Build Identifier: Mozilla/5.0 (X11; U; Linux x86_64; en-US; rv:1.9.2.13) Gecko/20110109 Iceweasel/3.6.13 (like Firefox/3.6.13)

CSS size property of a table in the form of for example:
    height: 100%;
is ignored (the result is the same as it would be "auto" or ommited).



Reproducible: Always

Steps to Reproduce:
Have some CSS like this:

div.tableContainer {
    position: absolute;
    height: 400px;
}

table.scrollTable {
    width: 490px;
    height: 100%;
/* 
adding this makes it work identical in Firefox and Chromium (but then its not what its meant to be
    display: block;
*/
}

And a TABLE inside a DIV like this:

<DIV class="tableContainer">
<TABLE class="scrollTable">

... rest of table code ...

</TABLE>
</DIV>
Actual Results:  
The height of the TABLE box is whatever the whole table takes-up.

Expected Results:  
The height of the TABLE box should be 400px - the height of the containing block.

When I submit the but, I will attach a sample complete HTML code which reproduces it. In Google Chromium 9.0.597.19 (68937) it works as I would expect it to.

